results.name: Decimal expansion of the volume of an icosahedron with unit edge length.
link: Ivan Panchenko, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
formula: Equals 5*phi^2/6, phi being the golden ratio. - _Stanislav Sykora_, Nov 23 2013
xref: Cf. A001622 (phi), A020829 (regular tetrahedron volume), A131594 (regular octahedron volume), A102769 (regular dodecahedron volume).
